{
  "doc_id": "32348",
  "text": "It has not yet been determined whether any specific type of DES is more likely to develop stent thrombosis. A direct comparison of the stent thrombosis rate between sirolimus-and paclitaxel-eluting stents in clinical trials may not reflect the true thrombogenicity, because of the differences in patient and lesion characteristics. Several meta-analyses revealed similar incidences of stent thrombosis between the two types of stents. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] The present study showed that implantation of a paclitaxel-eluting stent was a predictor of stent thrombosis. However, this result was not generalized because the number of patients was small and this study was not randomized.",
